{"key":"processedPost-12521738","value":{"id":12521738,"first":12521381,"last":12521738,"when":1273252995,"utime":"05/07/10 08:23 PM","content":"Depending on the substrate, if you're holding it down under water, start with an hour and then on subsequent substrates, go up from there if necessary.<br />I only soak sawdust substrate blocks for an hour, even though stamets recommends 24 to 36 hours.&nbsp; I've found by experience if you over-hydrate a substrate it performs poorly, so you're better off to get smaller fruits sooner and then re-soak, rather than risking over-hydration which leads to little or no fruits at all and green molds.&nbsp; You can easily tell how much water has been absorbed by weighing the substrate before and after soaking.<br />RR","title":"Re: Dunking a tray?"}}